# Assignment 5 – Static Routing

## Objective
To configure static routing between two networks so that devices can communicate.

---

## Theory
Routing is the process of forwarding packets between networks.

Static routing is a method where routes are manually configured by the network administrator. It is simple and suitable for small networks.

---

## Network Setup
Devices used:
- 2 Routers (R1, R2)
- 2 Switches
- 2 PCs

---

## IP Addressing

| Device | Interface | IP Address | Subnet Mask |
|--------|----------|------------|-------------|
| R1 | Fa0/0 | 192.168.1.1 | 255.255.255.0 |
| R1 | Serial | 10.0.0.1 | 255.255.255.252 |
| R2 | Serial | 10.0.0.2 | 255.255.255.252 |
| R2 | Fa0/0 | 172.16.0.1 | 255.255.0.0 |
| PC1 | NIC | 192.168.1.100 | 255.255.255.0 |
| PC2 | NIC | 172.16.0.100 | 255.255.0.0 |

---

## Configuration

### Router R1

enable
configure terminal
interface fastEthernet 0/0
ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown

interface serial 1/0
ip address 10.0.0.1 255.255.255.252
clock rate 64000
no shutdown

ip route 172.16.0.0 255.255.0.0 10.0.0.2


---

### Router R2

enable
configure terminal
interface serial 1/0
ip address 10.0.0.2 255.255.255.252
no shutdown

interface fastEthernet 0/0
ip address 172.16.0.1 255.255.0.0
no shutdown

ip route 192.168.1.0 255.255.255.0 10.0.0.1


---

## PC Configuration

### PC1
- IP Address: 192.168.1.100  
- Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.0  
- Default Gateway: 192.168.1.1  

### PC2
- IP Address: 172.16.0.100  
- Subnet Mask: 255.255.0.0  
- Default Gateway: 172.16.0.1  

---

## Verification
Use ping command:


ping 172.16.0.100


or


ping 192.168.1.100


---

## Result
Communication between both networks was successful using static routing.

---

## Conclusion
Static routing provides a simple method to connect networks where routes are fixed 
